Romantha Botha, Netwerk24Richard Weeks (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A Cape Town mother knew her son was going to commit suicide after receiving a goodbye message from him. &ldquo;When I received his message saying his final goodbyes, I knew he was going to commit suicide,&rdquo; a devastated Heidi Weeks, 50, said of her 22-year-old son Richard. He fell to his death on Table Mountain on Tuesday. He was her only child,&nbsp;Netwerk24&nbsp;reported.&ldquo;That&rsquo;s how he was. If he said he was going to do something, there was no turning back.&rdquo;She said he hadn&rsquo;t been his usual&nbsp;self when he got home after work on Monday.&nbsp;&ldquo;I asked him what was wrong, but he didn&rsquo;t answer me. He just ate his supper and went to bed. When he left for work the following day, I still reminded him to take his lunch. However, he said he&rsquo;d get something to eat at work. Little did I know these would be his last words to me.&rdquo; &nbsp;Weeks received a call around 10:00, saying he had not arrived at work.&nbsp;&ldquo;When I got a message from him, sent to me and his friends, I knew he was going to take his own life.&rdquo;In the message he said he knew what he was doing and asked that those left behind to forgive him.Weeks said she and her son were &ldquo;inseparable and best friends&rdquo;.A single parent, she&nbsp;said Richard missed his father.&nbsp;&ldquo;We&rsquo;d moved from Krugersdorp to Somerset West because I&rsquo;d wanted to give him a better life. He was a successful and independent young man and had bought his own car for his 21st birthday.&rdquo;Weeks said she was waiting for the results of the post mortem to confirm it was Richard&rsquo;s body.&ldquo;I&rsquo;m 99% certain that it&rsquo;s my son. It was his car and the clothes on the body were his.&rdquo;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.